# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# The network DIRECTORY is the root `/` now (it lists every watershed-point site). The live
# site (Lima) lives at /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co; coming-soon sites at /network/<slug>;
# the live site's investigation is a *story* at /stories/project-bosc (guided walk, flattened
# chapters); research moved to /research/hypotheses. These keep every old, deployed URL working.
#
# NETWORK-GLOBAL pages live at the root and are NOT rewritten — /about, /about-me, /wiki/*, /ask,
# /submit (the network-tier lead form), /basin, and the API (/api/*).
#
# IMPORTANT — on Cloudflare Pages a redirect ALWAYS fires before a matching static asset. So a
# broad `/<x>/*` rule shadows real files under that path. Consequences encoded in the order below:
#  - NO rule for `/`: it's the real directory hub now (served statically).
#  - NO `/submit` / `/research` / `/network/*` broad rules: those are real pages now.
#  - `/walk/crops/*` is a 200 passthrough BEFORE `/walk/*` (teardown crops live at public/walk/crops).
#  - the per-directory sub-paths (hypotheses/basin/locked-preview) come BEFORE the `/directory/*`
#    catch-all that maps the old coming-soon URLs onto /network/<slug>.

# Teardown crops — serve as-is before any /walk redirect.
/walk/crops/*           /walk/crops/:splat                                                     200

# The old /directory tree → its new homes. Specific sub-paths first, then the coming-soon catch-all.
/directory/hypotheses   /research/hypotheses                                                   301
/directory/basin        /basin                                                                 301
/directory/locked-preview  /locked-preview                                                     301
/directory/*            /network/:splat                                                         301
/directory              /                                                                      301

# /bosc -> /network/<id>, and the story moved to /stories/project-bosc (chapters flattened).
/bosc/start             /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc            301
/bosc/intro             /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc            301
/bosc/walk              /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc/contents   301
/bosc/walk/*            /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc/:splat     301
/bosc                   /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/                                301
/bosc/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/:splat                          301

# Even-older root-level legacy URLs (pre-/bosc) — straight to the new paths.
/start                  /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc            301
/timeline               /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/timeline                        301
/site/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/site/:splat                     301
/watershed/*            /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/watershed/:splat                301
/docs/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/docs/:splat                     301
/reports/*              /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/reports/:splat                  301
/walk/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc/:splat     301

# Old network-hub URLs (pre-#402, when the hub was /network). The hub is now `/`; research is
# /research/hypotheses. Exact rules only — /network/<slug> is real coming-soon content.
/network                /                                                                      301
/network/hypotheses     /research/hypotheses                                                   301
